OJECT_DIR` env var\\n- **Session ID**: Uses Cursor's `conversation_id` field (primary) or falls back to `session_id`\\n\\n#### 3. **Hook System**\\nCursor stores hooks in `.cursor/hooks.json` (camelCase keys):\\n\\n```\\n{\\n  \\\"version\\\": 1,\\n  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n    \\\"sessionStart\\\": [...],\\n    \\\"sessionEnd\\\": [...],\\n    \\\"beforeSubmitPrompt\\\": [...],\\n    \\\"stop\\\": [...],\\n    \\\"preCompact\\\": [...],\\n    \\\"subagentStart\\\": [...],\\n    \\\"subagentStop\\\": [...]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Hook Names** (become CLI subcommands):\\n- `session-start` → `SessionStart` event\\n- `before-submit-prompt` → `TurnStart` event\\n- `stop` → `TurnEnd` event\\n- `session-end` → `SessionEnd` event\\n- `pre-compact` → `Compaction` event\\n- `subagent-start` → `SubagentStart` event\\n- `subagent-stop` → `SubagentEnd` event\\n\\n**Hook Installation**:\\n- `InstallHooks()` - Idempotent, preserves unknown fields and user hooks\\n- `UninstallHooks()` - Removes Entire hooks, preserves other hooks\\n- `AreHooksInstalled()` - Checks `.cursor/hooks.json` for Entire hooks\\n- Supports `localDev` mode: `go run ${CURSOR_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks cursor <verb>`\\n- Detects Entire hooks by command prefix (`entire ` or `go run ${CURSOR_PROJECT_DIR}/...`)\\n\\n#### 4. **Transcript Format**\\n- **Format**: JSONL (one JSON object per line)\\n- **Key Difference from Claude Code**: Uses `\\\"role\\\"` field instead of `\\\"type\\\"`\\n- **Structure**: User messages use `<user_query>` tags wrapping text\\n- **Example Line**:\\n  ```json\\n  {\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"content\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"<user_query>\\\\nhello\\\\n</user_query>\\\"}]}}\\n  ```\\n- **Chunking**: Uses JSONL chunking (splits at line boundaries)\\n- **No tool_use blocks**: Unlike Claude Code, Cursor transcripts don't contain `tool_use` blocks, so file detection relies on git status instead\\n\\n#### 5. **Session Management**\\n- **ReadSe