e transitions, file detection, checkpoint saving, metadata generation). The flow is:\\n     8→\\n     9→```\\n    10→Agent hook invocation → ParseHookEvent() → Event → DispatchLifecycleEvent() → framework actions\\n    11→```\\n    12→\\n    13→An agent never calls strategy methods or manages session state directly. It only answers questions: \\\"What event just happened?\\\" and \\\"What does the transcript say?\\\"\\n    14→\\n    15→## Quick Reference\\n    16→\\n    17→### Core Interface (`Agent`)\\n    18→\\n    19→Every agent must implement all 19 methods on the `Agent` interface:\\n    20→\\n    21→| Group | Method | Purpose |\\n    22→|-------|--------|---------|\\n    23→| **Identity** | `Name()` | Registry key (e.g., `\\\"claude-code\\\"`) |\\n    24→| | `Type()` | Display name for metadata (e.g., `\\\"Claude Code\\\"`) |\\n    25→| | `Description()` | Human-readable description for UI |\\n    26→| | `DetectPresence()` | Check if agent is configured in the repo |\\n    27→| | `ProtectedDirs()` | Directories to preserve during rewind |\\n    28→| **Event Mapping** | `HookNames()` | Hook verbs that become CLI subcommands |\\n    29→| | `ParseHookEvent()` | **Core contribution surface** - translate native hooks to Events |\\n    30→| **Transcript** | `ReadTranscript()` | Read raw transcript bytes |\\n    31→| | `ChunkTranscript()` | Split large transcripts at format-aware boundaries |\\n    32→| | `ReassembleTranscript()` | Recombine chunks into a single transcript |\\n    33→| **Session Management** | `GetHookConfigPath()` | Path to hook config file |\\n    34→| | `SupportsHooks()` | Whether agent supports lifecycle hooks |\\n    35→| | `ParseHookInput()` | Parse hook callback input from stdin |\\n    36→| | `GetSessionID()` | Extract session ID from hook input |\\n    37→| | `GetSessionDir()` | Where agent stores session data |\\n    38→| | `ResolveSessionFile()` | Path to session transcript file |\\n    39→| | `ReadSession()` | Read session data from agent's storage |\\n    40→| | `WriteSession()` | Write session data for resumption |\\n    41→| | `FormatResumeCommand()` | Command to resume a session |\\n    42→\\n    43→### Optional Interfaces\\n    44→\\n    45→| Interface | Methods | When to implement |\\n    46→|-----------|---------|-------------------|\\n    47→| `HookSupport` | `InstallHooks`, `UninstallHooks`, `AreHooksInstalled`, `GetSupportedHooks` | Agent uses a config file for hook registration (e.g., `settings.json`) |\\n    48→| `HookHandler` | `GetHookNames` | **Required for CLI hook registration** — `entire hooks <agent> <verb>` subcommands are only created for agents implementing this interface. Typically delegates to `HookNames()`. |\\n    49→| `TranscriptAnalyzer` | `GetTranscriptPosition`, `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset`, `ExtractPrompts`, `ExtractSummary` | You want richer checkpoints with transcript-derived file lists and prompts |\\n    50→| `TranscriptPreparer` | `PrepareTranscript` | Agent writes transcripts asynchronously and needs a flush/sync step |\"}]},\"uuid\":\"727d532a-44fd-4c3d-92ce-dd009d523588\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-25T14:06:57.178Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/robin/Developer/cli/docs/architecture/agent-guide.md\",\"content\":\"# Agent Implementation Guide\\n\\nBefore implementing, read the [Agent Integration Checklist](agent-integration-checklist.md) for design principles (full transcript storage, native format preservation) and validation criteria.\\n\\n## Architecture Overview\\n\\nThe Entire CLI uses **inversion of control** for agent integration: agents are passive data providers that translate their native hook payloads into normalized lifecycle events, and the framework handles all orchestration (state transitions, file detection, checkpoint saving, metadata generation). The flow is:\\n\\n```\\nAgent hook invocation → ParseHookEvent() → Event → DispatchLifecycleEvent() → framework actions\\n```\\n\\nAn agent never calls strategy methods or manages session state directly. It only answers questions: \\\"What event just happened?\\\" and \\\"What does the transcript say?\\\"\\n\\n## Quick Reference\\n\\n### Core Interface (`Agent`)\\n\\nEvery agent must implement all 19 methods on the `Agent` interface:\\n\\n| Group | Method | Purpose |\\n|-------|--------|---------|\\n| **Identity** | `Name()` | Registry key (e.g., `\\\"claude-code\\\"`) |\\n| | `Type()` | Display name for metadata (e.g., `\\\"Claude Code\\\"`) |\\n| | `Description()` | Human-readable description for UI |\\n| | `DetectPresence()` | Check if agent is configured in the repo |\\n| | `ProtectedDirs()` | Directories to preserve during rewind |\\n| **Event Mapping** | `HookNames()` | Hook verbs that become CLI subcommands |\\n| | `ParseHookEvent()` | **Core contribution surface** - translate native hooks to Events |\\n| **Transcript** | `ReadTranscript()` | Read raw transcript bytes |\\n| | `ChunkTranscript()` | Split large transcripts at format-aware boundaries |\\n| | `ReassembleTranscript()` | Recombine chunks into a single transcript |\\n| **Session Management** | `GetHookConfigPath()` | Path to hook config file |\\n| | `SupportsHooks()` | Whether agent supports lifecycle hooks |\\n| | `ParseHookInput()` | Parse hook callback input from stdin |\\n| | `GetSessionID()` | Extract session ID from hook input |\\n| | `GetSessionDir()` | Where agent stores session data |\\n| | `ResolveSessionFile()` | Path to session transcript file |\\n| | `ReadSession()` | Read session data from agent's storage |\\n| | `WriteSession()` | Write session data for resumption |\\n| | `FormatResumeCommand()` | Command to resume a session |\\n\\n### Optional Interfaces\\n\\n| Interface | Methods | When to implement |\\n|-----------|---------|-------------------|\\n| `HookSupport` | `InstallHooks`, `UninstallHooks`, `AreHooksInstalled`, `GetSupportedHooks` | Agent uses a config file for hook registration (e.g., `settings.json`) |\\n| `HookHandler` | `GetHookNames` | **Required for CLI hook registration** — `entire hooks <agent> <verb>` subcommands are only created for agents implementing this interface. Typically delegates to `HookNames()`. |\\n| `TranscriptAnalyzer` | `GetTranscriptPosition`, `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset`, `ExtractPrompts`, `ExtractSummary` | You want richer checkpoints with transcript-derived file lists and prompts |\\n| `TranscriptPreparer` | `PrepareTranscript` | Agent writes transcripts asynchronously and needs a flush/sync step |\",\"numLines\":50,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":1102}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"b930b416-92e0-4c87-a535-2bc15856fbb7\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"727d532a-44fd-4c3d-92ce-dd009d523588\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/robin/Developer/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"0a6fa8ce-14c1-4d76-b8cd-3e2d721777e9\",\"version\":\"2.1.49\",\"gitBranch\":\"rwr/cursor-docs\",\"slug\":\"serialized-growing-starfish\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01LBVuTrB3cKfyMpK6VGMoEG\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01DcSxzGEHJZnZpMS9gHjDnS\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/robin/Developer/cli/docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md\",\"limit\":50},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":893,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":82866,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":893},\"output_tokens\":8,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYUv88AADqeXnG9VBXSPr\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"ac4052d5-23ef-4c9f-a59c-4e76c4701173\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-25T14:06:57.686Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"ac4052d5-23ef-4c9f-a59c-4e76c4701173\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/robin/Developer/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"0a6fa8ce-14c1-4d76-b8cd-3e2d721777e9\",\"version\":\"2.1.49\",\"gitBranch\":\"rwr/cursor-docs\",\"slug\":\"serialized-growing-starfish\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Read\",\"command\":\"callback\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01DcSxzGEHJZnZpMS9gHjDnS\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01DcSxzGEHJZnZpMS9gHjDnS\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-25T14:06:57.693Z\",\"uuid\":\"c867095a-1f50-48da-86d8-46cbe75eef36\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"ac4052d5-23ef-4c9f-a59c-4e76c4701173\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/robin/Developer/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"0a6fa8ce-14c1-4d76-b8cd-3e2d721777e9\",\"version\":\"2.1.49\",\"gitBranch\":\"rwr/cursor-docs\",\"slug\":\"serialized-growing-starfish\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01DcSxzGEHJZnZpMS9gHjDnS\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Agent Integration Checklist\\n     2→\\n     3→This document provides requirements and a checklist for integrating new AI coding agents with Entire. Use this to validate your implementation is correct and complete.\\n     4→\\n     5→For step-by-step implementation instructions, code templates, and testing patterns, see the [Agent Implementation Guide](agent-guide.md).\\n     6→\\n     7→## Core Principle: Full Transcript Storage\\n     8→\\n     9→Entire stores the **complete session transcript** at every checkpoint, not incremental diffs. This enables:\\n    10→\\n    11→- Simple rewind: restore the full transcript, agent resumes from that state\\n    12→- No dependency on previous checkpoints being intact\\n    13→- Consistent behavior across all checkpoint types (committed, uncommitted)\\n    14→\\n    15→**Each checkpoint must contain the full session history up to that point.**\\n    16→\\n    17→## Core Principle: Native Format Preservation\\n    18→\\n    19→Store transcripts in the **agent's native format**. Any transformation or normalization should only be done to support CLI features (rewind, resume, summarization, file extraction), not for backend or web UI consumption.\\n    20→\\n    21→**Why:**\\n    22→- The backend/web UI should handle format differences, not the CLI\\n    23→- Transforming for downstream consumers couples the CLI to their requirements\\n    24→- Native formats ensure compatibility with agent's own import/export tools\\n    25→- Reduces risk of data loss from lossy transformations\\n    26→- Format changes that break the UI can be fixed with a backend deploy; CLI changes require a full release cycle and user adoption\\n    27→\\n    28→**Do:**\\n    29→- Store the raw transcript as the agent produces it\\n    30→- Parse the native format when CLI features need specific data (e.g., extract file paths for `entire status`)\\n    31→- Let the backend normalize formats for display\\n    32→\\n    33→**Don't:**\\n    34→- Create a \\\"universal transcript format\\\" in the CLI\\n    35→- Transform logs to match what the web UI expects\\n    36→- Strip or restructure data to simplify backend processing\\n    37→- Create intermediate formats (e.g., converting JSON to JSONL for \\\"easier parsing\\\")\\n    38→- Reconstruct transcripts from events when a canonical export exists\\n    39→\\n    40→## Integration Checklist\\n    41→\\n    42→### Transcript Capture\\n    43→\\n    44→See Guide: [Transcript Format Guide](agent-guide.md#transcript-format-guide), [TranscriptAnalyzer](agent-guide.md#transcriptanalyzer), [TranscriptPreparer](agent-guide.md#transcriptpreparer)\\n    45→\\n    46→- [ ] **Full transcript on every turn**: At turn-end, capture the complete session transcript, not just events since the last checkpoint\\n    47→- [ ] **Resumed session handling**: When a user resumes an existing session, the transcript must include all historical messages, not just new ones since the plugin/hook loaded\\n    48→- [ ] **Use agent's canonical export**: Prefer the agent's native export command (e.g., reading Claude's JSONL file, Gemini's JSON) over manually reconstructing from events\\n    49→- [ ] **No custom formats**: Store the agent's native format directly in `NativeData` - do not convert between formats (e.g., JSON to JSONL) or create intermediate representations\\n    50→- [ ] **Graceful degradation**: If the canonical source is unavailable (e.g., agent shutting down), fall back to best-effort capture with clear documentation of limitations\"}]},\"uuid\":\"55d019d9-06db-4c45-bd0d-e4a4f5cc6372\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-25T14:06:57.692Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/robin/Developer/cli/docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md\",\"content\":\"# Agent Integration Checklist\\n\\nThis document provides requirements and a checklist for integrating new AI coding agents with Entire. Use this to validate your implementation is correct and complete.\\n\\nFor step-by-step implementation instructions, code templates, and testing patterns, see the [Agent Implementation Guide](agent-guide.md).\\n\\n## Core Principle: Full Transcript Storage\\n\\nEntire stores the **complete session transcript** at every checkpoint, not incremental diffs. This enables:\\n\\n- Simple rewind: restore the full transcript, agent resumes from that state\\n- No dependency on previous checkpoints being intact\\n- Consistent behavior across all checkpoint types (committed, uncommitted)\\n\\n**Each checkpoint must contain the full session history up to that point.**\\n\\n## Core Principle: Native Format Preservation\\n\\nStore transcripts in the **agent's native format**. Any transformation or normalization should only be done to support CLI features (rewind, resume, summarization, file extraction), not for backend or web UI consumption.\\n\\n**Why:**\\n- The backend/web UI should handle format differences, not the CLI\\n- Transforming for downstream consumers couples the CLI to their requirements\\n- Native formats ensure compatibility with agent's own import/export t